    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1897-07-05T09:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1897-07-03T00:00:00-05:00" n="133"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d133">
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Porter</persName> to Mr. <persName
                            type="to">Sherman</persName>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Embassy of the United States</hi>,<lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Paris</hi>
                        </placeName>. [<date
                            ana="#date_undated-inferred-from-document-content-and-sibling-dates"
                            calendar="gregorian" notAfter="1897-07-05T09:00:00-05:00"
                            notBefore="1897-07-03T00:00:00-05:00">undated</date>.] (Received July
                        5—9 a.m.)</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Telegram received. Wrote full particulars in dispatch of 28th. Have talked
                    further with most influential members of Government, and all <pb facs="0166"
                        n="132" xml:id="pg_132"/> feel that Government will not support the bills
                    and they are not likely to pass. Am watching them carefully.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Porter.</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
